t of dreams described in soaring verse. Pavlova subtly speaks against the limitations placed on women and especially women writers, which translator Barbara Heldt highlights in a critical introduction. Among the greatest works of literature by a Russian woman writer, A Double Life is worthy of a central place in the Russian canon.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aAristocracy (Social class)zRussiavFiction. 0aEnglish fictionxTranslations from Russian. 0aRussian fictionxTranslations into English. 0aWomen poets, RussianvFiction. 0aYoung womenzRussiavFiction. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Russian & Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh1 aGreen, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreen, Daniel.1 aHeldt, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeldt, Barbara.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065195908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishz978311061036908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/pavl1907840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231549110423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231549110.jpg  a978-3-11-061036-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065195-9  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  